UN investigators on Monday accused Burundi&#8217;s government of crimes against humanity, including executions and torture, and urged the International Criminal Court to open a case &#8220;as soon as possible&#8221;.The UN Commission of Inquiry on Burundi said it had &#8220;reasonable grounds to believe that crimes against humanity have been committed and continue to be committed in Burundi,&#8221; and pointed a finger at &#8220;the highest level of the state&#8221;.AFP 